The paper deals with the composition of two-way transducers, which are commonly studied in the field of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also introduces a new class of transducers called reversible transducers, which have applications in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the complexity of the composition of transducers, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and logic (cs.LO).
